value.title: Biden’s stern warning: ‘You cannot be traveling during … holidays’
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden says he doesn’t “want to scare anybody,” but he’s pleading with Americans to not travel during the upcoming holiday season.

value.title: Biden DHS pick had 'inappropriate' involvement in drug trafficker's commutation: Investigation
value.excerpt: Alejandro Mayorkas has admitted to making a mistake in weighing in on the case.

value.title: Dianne Feinstein says she backs Padilla to replace Harris in Senate
value.excerpt: Democratic Sen. Diane Feinstein said she backs California Secretary of State Alex Padilla to fill Kamala Harris' US Senate seat when she is sworn in as vice president in January.

value.title: Obama accuses Republicans of 'bait-and-switch' on deficit, urges 'bold government steps' from Biden
value.excerpt: Former President Obama argued on Wednesday that Republicans would hypocritically warn about the fiscal impact of economic recovery proposals after passing deficit-inducing tax cuts under President Trump.

value.title: Trump backs McConnell's Republican COVID-19 relief package: Mnuchin
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump will sign coronavirus relief legislation proposed by Republican Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell, Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin told reporters on Wednesday, should the proposed package pass the U.

value.title: Biden to meet with U.S. workers hit by pandemic, says Congress must act
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden will talk with workers and business owners on Wednesday about how the coronavirus has affected them as he prepares to confront his highest priority on taking office: the resurgent pandemic in the United States.

value.title: NAACP warns Biden over Rahm Emanuel rumors
value.excerpt: The NAACP became the latest progressive group to warn President-elect Joe Biden against adding former Chicago Mayor Rahm Emanuel to his Cabinet.

value.title: John Mulaney says he was investigated by the Secret Service over joke 'that was not about Donald Trump'
value.excerpt: John Mulaney says he was investigated by the Secret Service after making a joke that many believed was a threat against President Donald Trump.

value.title: Top pro-GOP PAC launching new initiative to counter Biden's 'far-left policies'
value.excerpt: A leading outside group that supports Republican causes is firing up a new initiative to counter what it says will be the "far-left policies" of President-elect Joe Biden's incoming administration.

value.title: Biden should pull off executive order 'blitz' before people can react, leftists say
value.excerpt: Some on the left are suggesting President-elect Joe Biden should sign executive orders and ram through policies as soon as possible -- before the media can fully cover things and give leeway for backlash.

value.title: Wisconsin governor: Trump election lawsuit an 'assault on democracy'
value.excerpt: Wisconsin Gov. Tony Evers (D) criticized President Trump’s latest lawsuit seeking to overturn the state's election results as an “assault on democracy.”

value.title: Obama suggests Trump's 'stereotypical macho style' appealed to some young Black voters
value.excerpt: Former President Obama said President Trump’s “stereotypical macho style” was to blame for his increase in Black male voters this election cycle.

value.title: ‘This is reality’: Renown doctor in Trump hospital garage retweet refutes fake claims
value.excerpt: Dr. Jacob Keeperman never expected his tweet to blow up on social media after it got hijacked by President Donald Trump.

value.title: CNN has been ‘overwhelmingly biased’ against Trump: Joe Concha
value.excerpt: You don't need behind-the-scenes tapes to know that CNN is anti-Trump because of how blatant the network coverage is, Fox News contributor Joe Concha told "America's Newsroom" Wednesday.

value.title: Trump's former campaign manager Brad Parscale said he planned to capitalize on baseless fears about mass voter fraud
value.excerpt: Trump has relentlessly spread false claims and conspiracy theories about mass voter fraud committed by Democrats.

value.title: In new interview, Mueller talks about Vietnam, but not Trump and Russia
value.excerpt: Mueller spoke to Chuck Rosenberg for the NBC News podcast The Oath. In the interview, Mueller seems more in command than when he spoke to Congress in 2019.

value.title: A Trump Fund-Raiser for Maya Wiley? Yes, but It’s Mary Trump
value.excerpt: Ms. Trump, the president’s niece, has written a tell-all book and opposed his re-election. Now she’s holding an online event for Ms. Wiley, who’s running for mayor of New York.

value.title: Trump vows defense bill veto unless internet liability shield scrapped
value.excerpt: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Tuesday he would veto the $740 billion National Defense Authorization Act unless it includes a measure eliminating a federal law protecting tech companies such as Facebook and Twitter.

value.title: Trump is leaving Washington as he governed — chaotically

value.title: Biden admits Dems 'forgot' rural America, says he did 'something good for the country' by beating Trump
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden said Democrats "forgot" rural America in an interview with New York Times opinion columnist Thomas L. Friedman published Wednesday.

value.title: Top Ga. voting official slams threats on election officers, tells Trump, senators to condemn it: 'Has to stop'
value.excerpt: A top Georgia voting official on Tuesday in a fiery press conference decried threats against Secretary of State Brad Raffensperger, the secretary's wife, and other elections officials and workers as the Trump campaign continues to fight the result of the presidential election in court.

value.title: As Trump Rages, Voters in a Key County Move On: ‘I’m Not Sweating It’
value.excerpt: Pre-election tensions ran high in Bucks County, Pa. But Biden supporters there are increasingly comfortable tuning President Trump out and moving on, with an eye toward January.

value.title: While Cuban-Americans in Florida came out big for Trump, Cubans stuck in Mexico pinned their hopes on Biden
value.excerpt: "I will remain hoping for a change. I'm glad Trump is out for good, and no thanks to my family in Florida," a Cuban doctor in Mexico told Insider.

value.title: William Barr breaks with Trump's election fantasy
value.excerpt: Attorney General William Barr just dealt the most credible blow to Donald Trump's lies about a stolen election, precisely because he previously often came across more as the President's personal lawyer than a neutral arbiter of justice.

value.title: Trump allies Barr, Giuliani at odds on discredited election fraud claims
